Llandyssul, Cardiganshire, Wales, Verenigd Koninkrijk"},"en":{"ABT 1124–":"about 1124–Deceased","1122–Female":"1122–Deceased","1123–Male":"1123–Deceased","1124–Male":"1124–Deceased","1126–Male":"1126–Deceased","1128–Male":"1128–Deceased","1140–Male":"1140–Deceased","1142–1242":"1142–1242","1170–Male":"1170–Deceased","1170–Female":"1170–Deceased","1176–Male":"1176–Deceased","1186–Female":"1186–Deceased","1160–Male":"1160–Deceased","1112–1165":"1112–1165","1110–Female":"1110–Deceased","1110":"1110","1165":"1165","1176":"1176","1242":"1242","1186":"1186","1142":"1142","1140":"1140","1160":"1160","1170":"1170","1128":"1128","1126":"1126","1124":"1124","1112":"1112","1123":"1123","ABT 1124":"about 1124","1122":"1122","about 1125":"about 1125","ABT    1160":"about 1160","Wales":"Wales","{Cdfr ap Dnwl}":"Ascoli Piceno, Marche, Italy","of Castell Hywel,Llandysul,Cardiganshire,Wales":"Llandyssul, Cardiganshire, Wales, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"ap","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Vietnamese Hung, Long, Minh, Muoi, Phan, Phat, Vinh, Cuong, Hien, Hoa, Lam, Lan.  Chinese Wing, Chi, Kin, Cheuk, Chi Wai, Chuen, Hon, Keung, Wah, Wai, Chiu, Ho.","Chinese: alternative Mandarin form of the surname 敖, see   Ao  .","Chinese: Cantonese form of the surnames 歐 and 區, see   Ou   1 and 2."],"variants":[{"name":"Auerbach","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Jewish Hyman, Moshe, Emanuel, Isidor, Bronia, Chaim, Faigy, Menachem, Meyer, Yechezkel.","German: habitational name from any of several places in southern Germany and Austria called Auerbach ‘the stream at the water meadow’. See also 2,   Au  , and   Bach  .","Jewish (Ashkenazic): habitational name from the town of Auerbach in the Upper Palatinate, Bavaria. Compare   Averbach  ."]},{"name":"Ao","meanings":["Chinese: Mandarin form of the surname 敖, meaning both ‘rambling’ and ‘deposed king without posthumous titles’ in ancient Chinese: (i) from the personal name of <i>Tai Ao</i> (太敖), teacher of the legendary king Zhuanxu (traditional dates: 2514–2437  BC ). (ii) it is said that the surname is also borne by descendants of deposed kings of the former state of Chu, with no posthumous titles, during the Spring and Autumn period (770–476  BC )."]},{"name":"Auer","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  German Alois, Hans, Erwin, Matthias, Siegfried, Bernd, Bernhard, Erna, Franz, Fritz, Hermann, Horst.","German (mainly Bavaria): topographic name for someone living by a water meadow, German <i>Au</i>, or a habitational name for someone from a place called Au or Aue (see   Au   and   Aue  ). This surname is also found in France (Alsace and Lorraine), Czechia, and Slovenia."]}]},{"name":"Rhydderch","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Recent revival of a traditional name meaning ‘reddish-brown’, which gave rise to the surname <i>Prothero(e)</i> (from <i>ap Rhydderch</i> ‘son of Rhydderch’). Though unrelated, it is commonly Anglicized as <b>Roderick</b>."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Llwyd","type":"FIRST","meanings":["Same as Lhuyd, q v."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Rhydderch Llwyd ap Cadifor Lord of Castell Hywel was born about 1124, his father, Cydifor Cadivor Ap Gwrgan, was 13 and his mother, Mallt verch LLywelyn Fychan of Carmarthenshire, was 16. He married Jennet ferch Aron of Cilsant Llanwinio. They were the parents of at least 1 son."},"et":{"ABT 1124–":"umbes 1124–Surnud","1122–Female":"1122–Surnud","1123–Male":"1123–Surnud","1124–Male":"1124–Surnud","1126–Male":"1126–Surnud","1128–Male":"1128–Surnud","1140–Male":"1140–Surnud","1142–1242":"1142–1242","1170–Male":"1170–Surnud","1170–Female":"1170–Surnud","1176–Male":"1176–Surnud","1186–Female":"1186–Surnud","1160–Male":"1160–Surnud","1112–1165":"1112–1165","1110–Female":"1110–Surnud","1110":"1110","1165":"1165","1176":"1176","1242":